---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="about -- alexander campos" description="I build things that protect how people think.">
  <article>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Alex. 26, central Virginia, first-gen Guatemalan American.
      I stay up too late.
    </p>

    <p>
      Most of what I make comes from the same impulse: I see a system,
      I find where it breaks people, and I build the thing that should
      already exist. That impulse doesn't turn off. It runs during the
      day when I'm mapping failure surfaces across regulatory operations
      at Capital One, and it runs at midnight while my wife sleeps and
      the French Bulldog holds down the other end of the couch.
    </p>

    <p>
      I get it from somewhere. Mom raised us and cleaned houses to make
      it work. Dad worked his way from cook to spending over two decades
      running blood transfusions in the OR. They never had the
      infrastructure. They were the infrastructure. Shout out mom
      and dad.
    </p>

    <p>
      I broke my spine and femur at 19. Months immobilized. I came out
      of it understanding that identity is something you rebuild, not
      something you're given -- and that lesson shows up in everything
      I've touched since. The forge metaphor in everything I name isn't
      decorative.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="/projects/guardian">Guardian</a> started because I
      noticed AI tools subtly rewriting how I described myself. Not
      overtly -- just enough to shift the framing over time. I wanted
      something that worked for me, not on me. That became a context
      protection system with a reframe detection engine. Then it
      surfaced a deeper problem, so I started building
      <a href="/projects/forgeframe">ForgeFrame</a> -- infrastructure
      for keeping your AI stack yours. The
      <a href="/projects/mcp-memory-server">memory layer</a> is open
      source. The governance layer is not. Some things shouldn't be
      commoditized.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm pursuing a Master of Engineering in AI Product Innovation.
      No CS degree -- I learned Python weeks before I shipped my first
      working system. I read Hofstadter, Marcus Aurelius, Spinoza, Ibn Khaldun,
      and too many others for someone who started as a bank teller --
      but I arrived at most of the frameworks before I found the names
      for them. The doubt keeps me honest. The work keeps moving.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm building for a future where my kids can safely thrive in a
      world full of things smarter than the safeguards around them.
    </p>

    <p>
      This site is hand-built because I think you should be able to
      read the source code of the person asking for your trust. View
      source. Open the console. The craft is the credential.
    </p>

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/notaprompt">GitHub</a> -- open source work</li>
      <li><a href="https://linkedin.com">LinkedIn</a> -- professional history</li>
      <li><a href="https://substack.com">Substack</a> -- writing on TRIM and cognitive architecture</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

